# Introduction This document provides a comprehensive overview of the system design, functionality, and architecture for the ProjectX platform. It is intended for new developers joining the project, technical reviewers, and contributors looking to understand the core components. ## System Overview ProjectX is a modular, scalable platform built with a microservices architecture. Each service is independently deployable and communicates through lightweight HTTP or messaging protocols. The backend is powered by Python-based services while the frontend is developed using a component-based JavaScript framework. ## Design Goals - Maintainability: Code is organized to be readable, testable, and adaptable to change. - Scalability: The system can handle increased load by scaling individual services horizontally. - Fault Tolerance: Failures in one service should not cascade across the system. - Observability: Logging, tracing, and monitoring are built into each service. ## Deployment Strategy The platform is containerized using Docker and orchestrated via Kubernetes. Configuration is managed through environment variables and secret management tools. CI/CD pipelines are implemented using GitHub Actions to ensure rapid and reliable delivery of updates. ## Directory Structure ``` projectx/ ├── services/ │ ├── auth/ │ ├── data/ │ └── gateway/ ├── frontend/ ├── infra/ └── README.md ``` ## Development Workflow 1. Clone the repository and create a new feature branch. 2. Implement your changes and write appropriate tests. 3. Run the test suite locally to ensure all checks pass. 4. Submit a pull request for review. ## License All code in this repository is licensed under the Apache 2.0 License.
